                <head>200. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>A memorandum for the Special Group charged with responsibility for fostering
                    insurrection in Cuba (Operation Mongoose), May 31, 1962, noted that at its
                    meeting on March 22, Attorney General <persName corresp="#p_KRF1">Robert
                        Kennedy</persName> had asked “what would be an appropriate course of action
                    for the United States to take in the event that the Soviets establish a military
                    base in Cuba.” The memorandum noted the Department of Defenseʼs concern over the
                    issue and proposed that each participating agency prepare a written response to
                        <persName corresp="#p_KJF1">Kennedy</persName>ʼs question. For text of the
                    memorandum, see <ref target="frus1961-63v10#pg_824">
                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations,</hi> 1961–1963 volume X, page
                    824</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
